
Imagine an intelligent plant watering app with features such as automatic watering, temperature and soil humidity tracking, daily weather forecasts, soil quality assessment, and light exposure recommendations. Users can set automated watering schedules based on plant needs, receive real-time weather alerts, and adjust watering plans accordingly. The app considers plant types for personalized care, measures soil humidity, and suggests amendments for soil health. It also integrates daily weather forecasts to adapt watering to changing conditions. Additionally, it provides insights into light exposure and maintains a history of activities for user evaluation.

